ometer (BD Biosciences) with 355, 405, 445, 488, 561, and 640nm lasers and equipped with 30 fluorescence detectors was utilized for flow cytometric measurements throughout this study.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1180788,"guid":"329BAE7098BF4F6C89CA7F27104B8A32","previous_id":1180787,"previous_guid":"8E74C70CD545447B928D4B74BB52E6DE","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"149D88F1C3084DCFA83A12E59D4DA965","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Staining"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"71053441554C48CD832E226A4F05954D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Intracellular pH was quantified by the Intracellular pH Calibration Buffer Kit (Cat. No. P35379).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1180789,"guid":"7345ECBDFE544428A1B371531F16424A","previous_id":1180788,"previous_guid":"329BAE7098BF4F6C89CA7F27104B8A32","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E4C34E4F10BE42EC8C4E4FDA26E5DB38","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Optimization of the intracellular pH measurement by flow cytometry "}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4BD4A7E99DD04439BB09A8595CDE3B53","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Calibration and measurement of intracellular pH<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#EA9F6C","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1180790,"guid":"A460C98C94C54C949B78F8A063A59BB6","previous_id":1180789,"previous_guid":"7345ECBDFE544428A1B371531F16424A","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B6AFF879BD2D482C8A58556E35B073B7","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Optimization of the intracellular pH measurement by flow cytometry "}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"CC2C80A29A094C3784491C77ED47A5A6","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">The Intracellular pH Calibration Buffer Kit (Cat. no. P35379) was used to clamp the intracellular pH with extracellular buffer.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#EA9F6C","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1180791,"guid":"BF3A9F9CA2FD4C0FACB24B111623908F","previous_id":1180790,"previous_guid":"A460C98C94C54C949B78F8A063A59BB6","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"06950DB311B54FDBBD8222FA428587B7","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Optimization of the intracellular pH measurement by flow cytometry "}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"A3B647F0F6CA4831ACB641EECA015528","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Four buffers are included in the kit, with pHs of 4.5, 5.5, 6.5, and 7.5. An average of three datapoints was plotted in the graph, and a linear trend line was fitted to obtain the pH standard curve error.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#EA9F6C","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1180792,"guid":"B26307DDF873470582EDEF14720BFEE6","previous_id":1180791,"previous_guid":"BF3A9F9CA2FD4C0FACB24B111623908F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"4B86B00E933D466AA085A4336446DEAE","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Optimization of the intracellular pH measurement by flow cytometry "}},{"id":1054724,"g